  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat </p>\n<p>Season the <strong>chicken thigh skins</strong> with <strong>salt </strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken</strong>, skin-side down and cook for 10 min, turning once</p>\n<p>Boil <span class=\"text-highlight\">a full kettle</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">While the chicken is cooking, cut</span> the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until they're fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and leave them to steam dry in a colander, keep the same pot for later!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">While the potatoes are cooking, chop the</span><strong><span class=\"text-highlight\"> chestnut</span> mushrooms</strong> in half</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong> </p>\n<p>Peel and slice the <strong>shallot</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> finely</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>parsley </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> skin</strong> is crispy, transfer the <strong>chicken</strong> to a baking tray, skin-side up</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-14 min or until the chicken is cooked through<span class=\"text-highlight\"> (no pink meat!)</span></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped mushrooms</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until they're browned and caramelised</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Knorr</strong></span> <strong>chicken stock cube</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/955.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Return</span> the reserved pot to a medium heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced shallot</strong> and <strong>drained potatoes</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the shallot is starting to caramelise</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> chopped parsley</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix until well coated – these are your <strong>parsley potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
